FT  28 OCT 93 / International Company News: BCE profits fall to CDollars
128m
BCE, the holding company which owns 100 per cent of Canada's biggest
telecommunications utility, Bell Canada, reported net profit of CDollars
128m (USDollars 98m), or 42 cents a share, in the third quarter against
CDollars 294m, or 96 cents, a share a year earlier on little changed
revenues of CDollars 5bn.
In the first nine months, BCE reported a loss of CDollars 218m, or 71 cents,
against a profit of CDollars 790m, or CDollars 2.56.
